The paper deals with evaluating question answering models using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves memory augmentation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The models being evaluated are neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.LG (Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves reasoning and tracking inconsistent states, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves image captioning, which could fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
